{"RECREANCE":[{"def":"Rec\"re*ance (rk\"r*ns), n.","pos":""}],"RECREANCY":[{"def":"The quality or state of being recreant.","pos":""}],"RECREANT":[{"def":"Crying for mercy, as a combatant in the trial by battle; yielding; cowardly; mean-spirited; craven.","pos":""},{"def":"Apostate; false; unfaithful.","pos":""}],"RECREATE":[{"def":"To give fresh life to; to reanimate; to revive; especially, to refresh after wearying toil or anxiety; to relieve; to cheer; to divert; to amuse; to gratify.","pos":""}],"RECREATION":[{"def":"The act of recreating, or the state of being recreated; refreshment of the strength and spirits after toil; amusement; diversion; sport; pastime.","pos":""}],"RECREATIVE":[{"def":"Tending to recreate or refresh; recreating; giving new vigor or animation; reinvigorating; giving relief after labor or pain; amusing; diverting.","pos":""}],"RECREMENT":[{"def":"Superfluous matter separated from that which is useful; dross; scoria; as, the recrement of ore.","pos":""}],"RECREMENTAL":[{"def":"Recrementitious.","pos":""}],"RECREMENTITIAL":[{"def":"Of the nature of a recrement.","pos":""}],"RECREMENTITIOUS":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to recrement; consisting of recrement or dross.","pos":""}],"RECRIMINATE":[{"def":"To return one charge or accusation with another; to chargeback fault or crime upon an accuser.","pos":""}],"RECRIMINATION":[{"def":"The act of recriminating; an accusation brought by the accused against the accuser; a counter accusation.","pos":""}],"RECRIMINATIVE":[{"def":"Re*crim\"i*na*tive (-n*tv), a.","pos":""}],"RECRIMINATOR":[{"def":"One who recriminates.","pos":""}],"RECRIMINATORY":[{"def":"Having the quality of recrimination; retorting accusation; recriminating.","pos":""}],"RECROSS":[{"def":"To cross a second time.","pos":""}],"RECRUDENCY":[{"def":"Re*cru\"den*cy (r*kr\"den*s), n.","pos":""}],"RECRUDESCE":[{"def":"To be in a state of recrudescence; esp.","pos":""},{"def":"Increased severity of a disease after temporary remission.","pos":""}],"RECRUDESCENT":[{"def":"Growing raw, sore, or painful again.","pos":""},{"def":"Breaking out again after temporary abatement or supression; as, a recrudescent epidemic.","pos":""}],"RECRUIT":[{"def":"To repair by fresh supplies, as anything wasted; to remedy lack or deficiency in; as, food recruits the flesh; fresh air and exercise recruit the spirits.","pos":""},{"def":"Hence, to restore the wasted vigor of; to renew in strength or health; to reinvigorate.","pos":""}],"RECRUITER":[{"def":"One who, or that which, recruits.","pos":""}],"RECRUITMENT":[{"def":"The act or process of recruiting; especially, the enlistment of men for an army.","pos":""}],"RECRYSTALLIZATION":[{"def":"The process or recrystallizing.","pos":""}],"RECRYSTALLIZE":[{"def":"To crystallize again.","pos":""}]}